    public interface IMoniker
    Arbitrary textual field that is guaranteed to never be directly interpreted by the platform. Monikers are provided to developers to store additional contextual data outside of the scope defined by the platform. A typical usage is to store an external system alias or key, linking the SMART COSMOS entity to an entity managed and stored outside of the platform.

    If a moniker value is assigned, it can be reset to its original (default) null value by passing in the special Field.NULL_MONIKER value. This special value is needed because the various levels of ViewType may preclude an instance from having the actual moniker value, and if that instance were submitted during an update operation it wouldn't be clear if the value was omitted in order to reduce network bandwidth consumption or if it was omitted because the developer actually wanted null assigned. The use of the special NULL_MONIKER solves this problem.
